*Job Type:* Full-time
*Working Hours:* 9:00 AM â 6:00 PM

   -

   ensure satisfaction and retention.
   -

   Collaborate with the marketing team to align campaigns and enhance sales
   performance.
   -

   using CRM tools.

   Meet or exceed weekly and monthly sales targets with a focus on quality
   client interactions.

Dear All,

It is with great pleasure and anticipation that I extend an invitation to
the official Opening Ceremony of the Robotics and Automation Student
Society (RAS).

This milestone event marks the beginning of a vibrant and collaborative
journey for our students, fostering excellence in the critical fields of
robotics, automation, and industrial technology.

*Event Details:*

   - Event: RAS Opening Ceremony
   - Date: Wednesday, October 22, 2025
   - Time: 9:00 AM to 12:00 PM
   - Venue: University Auditorium


Your presence at this ceremony is highly valued as a testament to the
university's commitment to student-led initiatives and advanced
technological education. We look forward to sharing our vision for society
with you.

 The opening ceremony features two exceptional industry leaders, offering a
truly unique and diverse perspective that will significantly benefit our
aspiring professionals:

*1. Mr. Shah Zuhairul Huda
*

*Global Connection: *Mr. Huda is a Senior Leader/Expert currently
based in* Texas,
USA*. His session will provide a crucial, direct link to the international
robotics and automation industry and the highly sought-after skills
required by US-based tech firms.

*Experience & Status: *As a professional with extensive experience in the
highly competitive global technology sector, his insights will illuminate
the potential for our students to pursue international careers and
understand cutting-edge industrial practices in a major global hub like
Texas.

*2. Mr. Syed Ali Ahmed
*

*Local Industry Depth:* Mr. Ahmed is an esteemed Industry Specialist/Expert
with deep roots and practical experience in the local and regional
automation sector.

*Direct Interaction: *His physical presence ensures students have the
opportunity for direct, face-to-face interaction, allowing them to ask
targeted questions and gain critical insights into immediate career
prospects and technological deployment within our region.

The combination of a high-status professional in Texas, USA, and a regional
expert guarantees a session that is both globally inspiring and locally
grounded. This is an invaluable opportunity for students to network and
envision their career paths.

We sincerely appreciate your efforts in encouraging student participation
and your dedication to their growth.

Thank you for your time and continued support.

Dear All,

Allow me first to extend our heartfelt felicitations from the *National
Centre for Cyber Security (NCCS)* at *Air University Islamabad, Pakistan*.
I am pleased to share with you the details about the *Pakistan
Cybersecurity Challenge (PCC) 2025*, an annual event organized by NCCS. The
PCC includes a *Hackathon/Capture-the-Flag Event*, the *Pak-Crypt National
Cryptography Challenge*, and the *Cybersecurity Ideas Cup*.



After the overwhelming success last three years events (PCC 2022-2024),
PCC-2025 is set to offer an even bigger platform for individuals and
students to *showcase their skills and dedication to securing Pakistan's
digital landscape*. It provides a unique opportunity to unleash the
talented youth of Pakistan.



In this regard, *Pak-Crypt National Cryptography Challenge 2025* is
specifically focused on mathematical and cryptography problems along with
their applications. It is open for students from *Schools, Colleges, and
Universities* all across Pakistan.



*Details of Pak-Crypt 2025 Challenge*



*Scope*
Pak-Crypt-2025 is focused on *Mathematics (**under 20 years: **Amateur
Category)* and *Cryptography (Professional Category)* along with their
applications.



*Eligibility Criteria*
Open to *all Pakistani nationals*.



*Competition Format*

Pak-Crypt-2025 will be completed in *three independent rounds*. Details are
as follows:

*Round 1: Registration and Screening (01 August â 25th October 2025)*

Open to all Pakistani nationals. Participants will complete registration
and an initial screening test. Top performers will qualify for Round 2.

*Round 2: Online Competition (25th October â 30th October 2025)*
The second round of Pak-Crypt will be conducted online. Participants who
qualify from Round 1 will have the opportunity to display their skills and
compete against other talented individuals.

*Round 3: On-Campus Final (26th â 27th November 2025)*
The final round of Pak-Crypt 2025 will be held on campus at NCCS, Air
University, Islamabad. *For all finalists, accommodation and free
registration in the International Cryptography Winter School and Cyber
Security Symposium will be provided. *

*Individual Prize Formula (Amateur & Professional):*

   - 1st Place: Rs. 200,000
   - 2nd Place: Rs. 150,000
   - 3rd Place: Rs. 100,000
   - All other finalists: Rs. 30,000â50,000 each

*For further details please visit:*

*Event Details:*
Pak-Crypt Challenge 2025

https://pakcrypt.org

*Registration Link:*
Pak-Crypt Registration 2025 

*Deadline for Registration:** 25th October, 2025*

Kindly disseminate to all the relevant faculty/ students. We look forward
to your support and participation from you esteemed organization. Thank you.

Dear Students,


Please note the following Missed Exam Policy:

*Missed Quizzes and Assignments:*

If a student misses a quiz or assignment, they will be awarded zero marks
for that particular assessment.

*Midterms and Final Examinations:*

There is a provision for a retake, in the case of:

*Eligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Marriage (self or sibling)

Â·         Severe illness requiring hospitalization

Â·         Death of an immediate family member

Â·         Severe injury affecting exam attendance

Â·         Iqama renewal or ISSB examination dates coinciding with the exam

Â·         Religious events with fixed dates (e.g., Hajj)

Â·         If you have more than 2 exams on the same day during the Exams.

*Ineligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Habitual applicants (more than 5 requests)

Â·         Applications with incomplete documentation

Â·         Minor illnesses (cold, flu, etc.)

Â·         Religious events with flexible dates (e.g., Umrah, Aitekaf)

Â·         Marriage of cousins or distant relatives

Â·         Any other reasons not covered in the eligibility criteria

*Important Notes:*

Â·         Students must submit their applications via *FLEX* with *supporting
documents* within the deadline. (No application will be considered manually
or after the deadline).

Â·         Those traveling for a valid reason may take the exam at a remote
campus on the same day and time as their base campus.

Â·         A Faculty Committee shall examine the student's request for a
repeat test/exam If retake of the final exam is allowed, it shall be held
as soon as possible, but not later than one week before the start of
next semester.

Â·         The final decision rests with the Campus Committee and the Campus
Director.



*Retake Exam Fee:*

The retake exam fee is payable before the examination in all the
above-mentioned cases. The late examination fee will be Rs. 2000/- per exam.
Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an application fee. This is
non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be charged on applications
that have been approved.

Dear Students,


Please note the following Missed Exam Policy:

*Missed Quizzes and Assignments:*

If a student misses a quiz or assignment, they will be awarded zero marks
for that particular assessment.

*Midterms and Final Examinations:*

There is a provision for a retake, in the case of:

*Eligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Marriage (self or sibling)

Â·         Severe illness requiring hospitalization

Â·         Death of an immediate family member

Â·         Severe injury affecting exam attendance

Â·         Iqama renewal or ISSB examination dates coinciding with the exam

Â·         Religious events with fixed dates (e.g., Hajj)

Â·         *If you have more than 3 exams on the same day during the Exams.*

*Ineligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Habitual applicants (more than 5 requests)

Â·         Applications with incomplete documentation

Â·         Minor illnesses (cold, flu, etc.)

Â·         Religious events with flexible dates (e.g., Umrah, Aitekaf)

Â·         Marriage of cousins or distant relatives

Â·         Any other reasons not covered in the eligibility criteria

*Important Notes:*

Â·         Students must submit their applications via *FLEX* with *supporting
documents* within the deadline. (No application will be considered manually
or after the deadline).

Â·         Those traveling for a valid reason may take the exam at a remote
campus on the same day and time as their base campus.

Â·         A Faculty Committee shall examine the student's request for a
repeat test/exam If retake of the final exam is allowed, it shall be held
as soon as possible, but not later than one week before the start of
next semester.

Â·         The final decision rests with the Campus Committee and the Campus
Director.



*Retake Exam Fee:*

The retake exam fee is payable before the examination in all the
above-mentioned cases. The late examination fee will be Rs. 2000/-
per exam. Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an application fee.
This is non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be charged on
applications that have been approved.

Hey Muhammad,

I want to share something that could get you hired before the year ends - or position you for the first wave of hires in January.

This is especially important if you've been rejected by a company you really wanted to work for.

I know that gut-punch feeling when you see, "We've decided to move forward with other candidates." That's exactly why I'm sharing this with you.

This strategy can help you turn that rejection into an acceptance at the same company - sometimes in just a few months.Â 

Or at minimum, it can get you a referral from a senior leader to another company, which means you skip the 250+ applicant line in January.

The strategy? Show up where they can't ignore you - at their events.
Â 
Now before you say "Jon, that's crazy"...
Â 
I've seen people get referrals from senior leaders they met at events - referrals that got them interviews at the same company that rejected them weeks earlier.
Â 

Here's why it works:

Recruiters filter resumes based on checkboxes and keywords. You might have been rejected for something completely fixable - not because you weren't qualified.

But if you meet senior leaders at events? They see you in a new light. Your communication skills, your passion, your cultural fit - all in real time.

When a director or hiring manager meets you in person and likes you, they can override earlier rejections. They can keep you top of mind, and they can refer you internally when new roles open.
Â 

Here's how to make it happen:

After getting rejected, don't just move on. Visit the company's website, LinkedIn, and social media to find upcoming events they're hosting or sponsoring.

Look for community outreach events, industry conferences, charity events, technical talks, or even trade shows.

Register as an attendee - not as a job seeker. Research who from the company will be there. Focus on decision-makers like VPs, directors, or department heads.
Â 
At the event, engage authentically. Have real conversations about industry challenges and innovations. Show your knowledge. Don't lead with "I applied for a job here."

If the conversation flows and the connection feels genuine, you can mention you recently applied. Frame it as admiration:

"I'm actually familiar with your company. I applied for a role recently because I'm passionate about the work you're doing in [specific area]."

That's how you show up where they can't ignore you.

Now here's the catch:
This only works if you're prepared. You need a strong resume, solid networking skills, and a guaranteed job search strategy.

That's exactly what my team and I help with at Wonsulting.

We're offering free career consultations where we'll identify what's holding you back and show you how to fix it.

Here's what happened last week: Our 10 consultation spots filled in under 48 hours.

So we opened 10 more spots this week.

If you're reading this before Tuesday, you still have a chance to grab one.

ð Book your free consultation here:Â âhttps://form.typeform.com/to/KQqdWmNS

The best January opportunities go to people who start preparing now - not in January when everyone else wakes up.
Â 
Â 
Talk soon,

Jonathan Javier
Co-Founder & CEO, Wonsulting

Dear Student,

Elite IT Team is seeking a passionate *AI Intern* to join team for a
3-month internship. This role is ideal for individuals who have explored
the world of Artificial Intelligence through hands-on projects and are
eager to gain practical experience in a fast-paced, real-world environment.
Youâll work on projects involving *Natural Language Processing (NLP)*,
*Computer
Vision*, and *Voicebots*, helping build functional prototypes using
*no-code* and *low-code* tools.

*Duration:* 3 Months (with potential extension based on performance)
*Salary Bracket:* PKR 20kâ30k
*Apply at:*  https://forms.gle/XLD7nT6UUup16dJ78
*Deadline:* 9th October 2025

*Key Responsibilities:*

   -

   Assist in building and training basic NLP, computer vision, or voicebot
   models.
   -

   Work with no-code platforms such as *Lovable* and *Bubble* to prototype
   AI-powered applications.
   -

   Create and connect automations using tools like *n8n*, *Make*, or
   *Zapier*.
   -

   Support the AI team with data collection, testing, and integration tasks.
   -

   Document workflows and assist in preparing demo materials for clients
   and internal presentations.

*Requirements:*

   -

   Basic understanding of NLP, computer vision, and AI model workflows.
   -

   Familiarity with voicebot development tools (e.g., *Dialogflow*,
   *ElevenLabs*, or similar).
   -

   Experience with no-code app builders (e.g., *Lovable*, *Bubble*).
   -

   Knowledge of automation tools such as *n8n*, *Make*, or *Zapier*.
   -

   Strong curiosity to learn, problem-solving attitude, and good
   communication skills.

*Nice to Have:*

   -

   Familiarity with *OpenAI*, *Hugging Face*, or other AI APIs.
   -

   Experience working with data or integrating APIs into no-code platforms.

*Perks:*

   -

   Hands-on experience on live client projects.
   -

   Mentorship from experienced AI developers and automation experts.
   -

   Internship certificate and potential for a full-time opportunity upon
   completion.

If youâre someone who loves experimenting with AI tools and building smart
systems without getting lost in the code, weâd love to hear from you!

Dear All,

Allow me first to extend our heartfelt felicitations from the *National
Centre for Cyber Security (NCCS)* at *Air University Islamabad, Pakistan*.
I am pleased to share with you the details about the *Pakistan
Cybersecurity Challenge (PCC) 2025*, an annual event organized by NCCS. The
PCC includes a *Hackathon/Capture-the-Flag Event*, the *Pak-Crypt National
Cryptography Challenge*, and the *Cybersecurity Ideas Cup*.



After the overwhelming success last three years events (PCC 2022-2024),
PCC-2025 is set to offer an even bigger platform for individuals and
students to *showcase their skills and dedication to securing Pakistan's
digital landscape*. It provides a unique opportunity to unleash the
talented youth of Pakistan.



In this regard, *Pak-Crypt National Cryptography Challenge 2025* is
specifically focused on mathematical and cryptography problems along with
their applications. It is open for students from *Schools, Colleges, and
Universities* all across Pakistan.



Details of Pak-Crypt 2025 challenge are:

*Scope*

Pak-Crypt-2025 is focused to the problems relevant to Mathematics,
Cryptography and their applications.



*Eligibility Criteria*

Any Pakistani national having interest in these areas except officials from
Government R&D and Strategic Organizations/Institutions.



*Competition Format*

Pak-Crypt-2025 will be completed in *three independent rounds*. Details are
as follows:

*Round 1: Registration and Screening (01 August â 30th September 2025)*

The first round is open to all Pakistani nationals. It involves a
registration process coupled with an initial screening test. The
registration process collects basic information about candidates, while the
test serves as an entry-level filter. Top qualifiers from Round 1 will be
announced before the mid of October and invited to compete in the second
round.

*Round 2: Online Competition (15 October â 30 October 2025)*
The second round of Pak-Crypt will be conducted *online*. Participants who
qualify from Round 1 will have the opportunity to *display their skills and
compete* against other talented individuals.
The qualifiers of Round 2 will be given the opportunity to register for
Round 3 as a *team of 1-2 persons* (both of whom must be Round 3 qualified).

*Note: Prizes will be equally shared among winning team members.*

*Round 3: On-Campus Final (26 â 27 November 2025)*
The final round of Pak-Crypt 2025 will be held *on campus at NCCS, Air
University, Islamabad*.

The *top teams* from the previous rounds will compete for *prestige and
prize money*.

*Event*

*Date*

Pre-Qualifier Round for PakCrypt Cryptography Competition

01-Aug-2025 to 30-Sept-2025

Qualifier Round for PakCrypt Cryptography Competition

15-Oct-2025 to 30-Oct-2025

Final Round

26-27 Nov, 2025

*Total Prize Pool: Rs. 3.0 Million+*

Prize money of *over Rs. 3.0 Million* will be distributed across the two
competition categories, including *Professional* and *Amateur*.



For further details please visit:

*Event Details:*
Pak-Crypt Challenge 2025


*Registration Link:*

Every Job Search Has 5 Stages

Imagine your job search as baking the perfect cake ð°

It seems complicated at first.
Ingredients everywhere, steps that could go wrong.Â 
Â 
But with the right recipe and persistence? You can create something amazing.
Â 
That's what we're giving you today: the complete recipe.Â 

The exact [5-stage system that's worked](https://app.wonsulting.ai/) for thousands of job seekers.
Â 
By the end of this email, you'll understand each stage and know how to identify where you are right now.

Plus, you'll discover the tool that creates your personalized roadmap once you're ready to begin.
Â 
[Get Your Personalized Job Search Plan â](https://app.wonsulting.ai/)

â

[Shadow]

Your Five Stages

Here's your complete roadmap:

Stage 1: Target Job
Pick one job title as your north star. Even if you'd be "good at 20 jobs," hiring managers only care if you're perfect for theirs. Focus beats volume every time.

Stage 2: Resume
Build a target resume that matches your target job. Aim for a ResumAI score above 75. Every bullet point should scream "I was born to do this exact job."

Stage 3: Applying
Use your target resume to apply to at least 50 job openings with your exact target job title. Because it matches, your callback chances rise dramatically.

Stage 4: Interview
No interviews after 50 applications? That's useful data! Go back to stage 2 and revise your resume or target job. Getting interviews? Perfect your story, practice with InterviewAI, and prep for tough questions.

Stage 5: Offer
Master negotiation, compare packages, and close the deal. Keep momentum going until you land the role you want.

The secret? Knowing exactly which stage you're in right now.

Most people get lost in Stage 3, applying everywhere without tracking what works. Others never finish step 1.

[Shadow]

The Cold Outreach Graveyard

Most networking attempts fail for one reason.

They ask before they give.
They're generic "pick your brain" requests that create work for strangers.

But what if you could prove you belong in just 75 words?

The secret: show you've done your homework, ask one precise question, and make the next step easy.

The Framework That Gets Replies

Here's the structure (75â120 words max):
Pinpointed Opener: Reference their work specifically.
Micro-Credential: One line proving you're a peer, not a fan.
The Question: Ask about a trade-off they likely faced.
Don't ask for career advice. Ask how they made a hard decision.
The Binary Fork: Offer an easy alternative.
The Graceful Exit: Thank them for their work.

Here's what this looks like in practice:

"Hi Marcus, I just read your breakdown of Stripe's pricing migration in your Q3 retrospective. Dear Students,



Please note the following Missed Exam Policy:



*Missed Quizzes and Assignments:*

If a student misses a quiz or assignment, they will be awarded zero marks
for that particular assessment.

*Midterms and Final Examinations:*

There is a provision for a retake, in the case of:

*Eligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Marriage (self or sibling)

Â·         Severe illness requiring hospitalization

Â·         Death of an immediate family member

Â·         Severe injury affecting exam attendance

Â·         Iqama renewal or ISSB examination dates coinciding with the exam

Â·         Religious events with fixed dates (e.g., Hajj)

Â·         If you have more than 2 exams on the same day during the Exams.

*Ineligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Habitual applicants (more than 5 requests)

Â·         Applications with incomplete documentation

Â·         Minor illnesses (cold, flu, etc.)

Â·         Religious events with flexible dates (e.g., Umrah, Aitekaf)

Â·         Marriage of cousins or distant relatives

Â·         Any other reasons not covered in the eligibility criteria

*Important Notes:*

Â·         Students must submit their applications via *FLEX* with *supporting
documents* within the deadline. (No application will be considered manually
or after the deadline).

Â·         Those traveling for a valid reason may take the exam at a remote
campus on the same day and time as their base campus.

Â·         A Faculty Committee shall examine the student's request for a
repeat test/exam If retake of the final exam is allowed, it shall be held
as soon as possible, but not later than one week before the start of
next semester.

Â·         The final decision rests with the Campus Committee and the Campus
Director.



*Retake Exam Fee:*

The retake exam fee is payable before the examination in all the
above-mentioned cases. The late examination fee will be Rs. 2000/- per exam.
Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an application fee. This is
non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be charged on applications
that have been approved.



*Regards,*

Class Activity - 22/10/2025
Two-page handwritten document explaining:


    - How the intellectual property infringement occurred.
    - What type of intellectual property was involved (patent, copyright, or  
trademark)?
    - The main arguments presented by both parties.
    - The verdict, or final decision, of the court.
    - Lessons learned for computing professionals about ethical and legal  
boundaries in software development.

available on the Internet. Each student is required to select case study  
from the provided list and complete the assigned activity accordingly.


    -  MGM vs. Grokster Case
    -  Sony Betamax Case
    - Samsung vs Apple (Design Patent Case)
    - Oracle vs Google (Java API Case)
    - Napster Copyright Infringement
    - Viacom vs YouTube (Copyright Case)
    - Adobe vs Christenson (Software Resale)
    - Turnitin Plagiarism Case
    - Look and Feel Lawsuit (Apple vs Microsoft)

Dear students,
Please read carefully, before filling-up the application form:

A student can only work either as a Student Lab Assistant (SLA) or Teaching
Assistant (TA) You cannot opt for both at same time.

- 1st Priority will be given to Senior Batch Students.
- 2nd Priority will be given to Junior Batch students.
- 3rd priority will be given to veterans.
- Minimum 3.0 GPA in your required subject for TA.


*Make sure to submit the form using your NUCES student Email ID (check and
re login with your NUCES email ID to prevent form access errors)*
- TA has to check at least 6 assessments (quizzes + assignments & course
project (if any), A course project is equivalent to 2 assessments.
- In case of online assignment submissions by the students, the TA has to
properly comment/assess the assignment in electronic format while grading.

- Less than 6 assessments will be paid less proportionally. (Rates are for
6 Assessments of A Student)

Payment will be made as per the following scheme for checking 6 assessments
of 1 student:
1) Rs. 250 for CS courses with programming assignments
2) Rs. 190 for CS courses Non programming assignments
3) Rs. 190 for MG courses
4) Rs. 150 for Math, Physics & Statistics courses

*Last Date to apply is Sunday, 14th September, 2025.*

night stays.



*Campus Facilities and Operating Hours*

Our campus operates on a schedule, time work designed to provide an optimal
environment for learning, teaching, and working during regular working
hours of university. While we strive to offer a wide range of facilities
and services to support your academic and professional pursuits.

of night stay, food or accommodation for stay for the officials, visitors,

informed not to demand any such facility from the university.

their schedules and arrangements accordingly. If you are in the campus for
academic or professional purposes, we encourage you to make necessary

The 60-Second Ghost Test

If it takes just a few minutes to apply to a job, it might not be worth it to check if it's real or not.
Â 
But for lengthy applications, it makes sense to invest a few minutes up front to make sure you're not wasting your time.
Â 
So before you apply, run this check.
Â 
â When was it posted?
Anything older than three weeks can be suspicious. Fresh posts, especially ones showing application counts or recent updates, prove something's actually moving.

Â 
â Stale listings that never change?
Skip them.Â They're corpses. Dead jobs just sitting there, collecting digital dust and your precious time.

Â 
â Can you see concrete details?
Real jobs have specifics. Hiring timeline. Interview process. Named recruiter. Salary range. Required location. Actual responsibilities you can picture yourself doing.

Â 
Ghost jobs hide behind vagueness like a "competitive salary" with no range.
Endless requirements describing a unicorn, not a human they actually want to hire.
Â 
Â

Think triage, not spray-and-pray.

Phase One: Quick Filter (60 seconds)

Three questions âï¸Â 
âï¸ Posted just once recently?
âï¸ Posted within three weeks?Â 
âï¸ Has specific details and salary info?

Â 
Fail two of these? Move on. Don't look back.

Â 
Â 
Phase Two: Verification (5-10 minutes)

Â 
âï¸ Search for duplicates.
Google the exact job title plus company name. If you find the same listing reposted monthly for six months, you've discovered a perma-post.

Â 
âï¸Â Check LinkedIn for recent hires.
âï¸Â Google for repost history.

Still unsure? Send a short message: "Hi [recruiter name], I'm interested in the [role]. Is this position actively being filled?"

Only now do you invest time in tailored resumes and cover letters, plus take-home assignments.Â Because now you've verified this job actually exists.

*Dear TLC Aspirants,*
*The Literary Club (TLC)* is thrilled to announce the
*induction interviews *to constitute its *Executive Committee*. Candidates
impassioned to serve the society by becoming a valued part of its hierarchy
can apply for the below posts:



1. President

2. Vice President

3. Secretary

4. General Secretary

3. Event Manager

4. Media & Promotion Head

5. Marketing Head

6. Guest relation Head

7. Treasurer

8. SOP Compliance Head



The interviews will be conducted in two sessions according to the following
schedule:



*Day 1*



Date: 25th August, 2025

Day: Monday

Time: 13:00-15:00

*Venue: EE, Conference Room *



*Day 2*



Date: 26th September, 2025

Day: Tuesday

Time: 12:00- 14:00

*Venue: EE Conference Room*



Important guidelines to take the interviews are as follows:


   1. Candidates must be well prepared with interviews.
   2. Candidates must bring a hard and soft copy of the properly filled
   selection form (attached to this email).
   3. One passport size photo must be attached with properly filled
   selection form (attached to this email).
   4. Candidates must be well prepared with their presentations on vision
   and tentative planning of the events to be conducted throughout the session
   (proposed events calendar, budget, strategies etc).
   5. Candidates must not be under any disciplinary warning.

*NOTE: You will be informed in case of a change of venue.*

   - * Please note that students who fail to submit this form will not be
   considered for the selection process.*
   - *You are requested to follow the given templates only.*

*Standard rules for eligibility of Student Executive body:*

   - Currently registered students with CGPA >=2.0 and without any
   Disciplinary Punishments / Warning.
   - Students should have at least one year of studies left when they are
   considered for any position in the Executive body.
   - *Re-admitted, Laggard or Fresh students will not be allowed in any
   student executive body.*
   - No student can bear office in more than one society simultaneously.
   - The Student Affairs Office will review the list of Student Executive
   bodies before final announcement.

Become the AI-Ready Hire They Need Now

We've got good news this July ð
Â 
While only 40% of companies are hiring overall, 51% of tech companies are actively recruiting right now.Â¹
Â

Companies investing in AI report the strongest hiring plans this quarter.Â²
Â

Â

Â 
This week's AI-ready toolkit
ð Resume transformation that screams "AI-savvy" (even if you're a beginner)
ð 3 AI upskilling moves that take 30 minutes to start

WONSULTING WISDOM

How to Add AI Skills to Your Resume

You're underselling yourself.

Most job seekers think AI skills require a computer science degree.
Â 
But if you've ever uploaded a spreadsheet to ChatGPT for analysis, you've just demonstrated practical AI application that 90% of managers can't do.

The problem isn't your skills. It's how you're describing them.

Here's the formula that gets interviews:

Step 1: Lead with the Human Spark
"Engineered custom ChatGPT prompts..." or "Built AI-powered workflow..."
Start with action, not acronyms.

Step 2: Name the Technique (Briefly)
This depends on your level:

- Beginner: "...using AI document analysis..."
- Intermediate: "...leveraging Retrieval-Augmented Generation..."
- Advanced: "...implementing custom vector search..."

Step 3: Drop the Business Impact
"...reducing report generation from 2 hours to 6 minutes."

Always end with numbers that make CFOs smile!

Here's What This Looks Like:
Â 
Starter: "Automated competitive analysis using ChatGPT document uploads, reducing research time from 4 hours to 30 minutes per client brief."
Â 
Intermediate: "Developed RAG-powered ChatGPT system integrating company documentation to automate client research, cutting preparation time from 3 hours to 15 minutes per discovery call."
Â 
Advanced: "Built custom vector database with OpenAI embeddings for real-time policy retrieval, enabling instant compliance answers and reducing legal review cycles by 60%."

Why This Works: You're showing technical fluency without technical intimidation. Recruiters see someone who can bridge the gap between cutting-edge AI and real business results.

Your Move: Pick your level and find one project where you used AI to solve a problem. Even if it was just summarizing meeting notes with Claude or analyzing survey data with ChatGPT.

Rewrite it using this formula. Post it on LinkedIn.

Because here's the reality: companies desperately need people who can make AI practical, not theoretical.

Your AI experiments are more valuable than you think!

LEVEL UP!

Three 30-Minute AI Wins That Land Interviews

Your competition just got smaller.

While others debate whether AI will replace them, smart job seekers are building AI skills that make them irreplaceable.Â 
Â 
Here's how to gain a meaningful advantage, often in as little as 30 minutes a day.

Sprint 1: Build Your Prompt Library (5 days)
Day 1: Copy 3 job descriptions into Claude.
Ask: "What are the 5 most common tasks in these roles?"
Get specific examples.
Days 2-4: Create prompts like: "Analyze this sales data and identify the top 3 actionable insights with supporting metrics." Test on real examples.
Day 5: Ask Claude: "How can I improve these prompts for better results?"
What you'll have: A reusable system that turns AI into your personal assistant.

Sprint 2: AI-Powered Portfolio Project (7 days)
Days 1-2: Ask Claude: "Find me 3 datasets relevant to [your industry] with clear business problems to solve."
Days 3-5: Upload data and prompt: "Walk me through analyzing this step-by-step. What insights should I highlight?"
Days 6-7: Ask: "How should I present this to show both AI collaboration and critical thinking?"
The result: Portfolio proof that you don't just use AI. You interpret results and drive decisions.

Sprint 3: Build Your First Automation (4+ days)
Day 1: Tell Claude: "I spend too much time on [specific task]. How can I automate this with Zapier?"
Days 2-3: Follow AI's step-by-step tutorial. Ask for troubleshooting help.
Day 4: Prompt: "Help me calculate ROI and document this for my resume."
Your outcome: A real automation plus a measurable resume bullet.

Pro-Tip: Stuck anywhere? Screenshots are your friend. Instead of typing what's wrong, share a screenshot and ask: "What am I missing?" or "What would an expert do differently?"

This works with Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini or any advanced AI.

Dear FAST-NUCES BS, MS, and PhD Students,
Summer School on Generative Artificial Intelligence (GENAI) for

ATTEND THE CESI SUMMER SCHOOL AND GET INVOLVED IN TOMORROWâS MAJOR
CHALLENGES LINKED TO GENERATIVE AI Introduction
Aimed at French and international students who are studying computer
science and industrial engineering, the Summer School is a training program
that immerses participants in the heart of the generative AI challenges in
Industry 5.0 and the factory of tomorrow
Its goal is to allow reflection, exchange, and sharing among French and
international students from all backgrounds on inputs linked to new models
of generative AI and the development of new AI tools.
This Summer School will not only allow you to discover new approaches and
technologies of generative AI and its industrial applications, but will
also offer you practical work conducted by renowned experts in their field.
Cultural visits to companies, laboratories, and emblematic locations will
complete the Program.

Attend a two-week program in France, from 7 to 18 July 2025, to develop and
deepen your knowledge in generative AI for Industry 5.0:
- Evolve and study in English in an intercultural environment,
- Discover and deepen generative AI techniques and their industrial
applications
- Discover new scientific and professional approaches to generative AI
(Prompt Engineering and Generative AI models)
- Discover the âFrench Techâ- Participate in cultural and technical visits
in Nice(eco-neighborhoods, companies, laboratories)
- Discover Nice, the capital of CÃ´te dâAzur, and benefit from cultural
immersion in France

Learning objectives

   -  Understanding the challenges of generative AI and its industrial
   applications
   - Understanding the challenges of generative AI (climate, environment,
   energy, ethics, responsibility, etc.)
   - This common thread project, with a case study, focuses on generative
   AI and its fundamental models for industrial applications in human-machine
   interaction, computer vision and quality control in an industrial process,
   etc.
   - Practical work on generative AI for the industrial revolution Fablab
   3D, AR/VR

 OBJECTIVES
Raising awareness of tomorrowâs challenges related to generative AI, and
all the major topics of Foundation Models and Linguistic Models (LLM), Deep
Learning (DL), Machine Learning (ML) for industrial applications, of
course, but also Natural Language Processing (NLP), the DL/ML revolution,
and computer vision for industrial applications.
PEDAGOGY
Completed Projects
The Summer School revolves around generative AI.
Common thread projects:
- Generative AI project and its fundamental models for industrial
application in human-machine interactions, computer vision and quality
control in an industrial process, etc.
- Practical work on generative AI for the industrial revolution
Requirements
 A B1 level in English is required with good academic results in the basic

*EXAMINATION RULES*



*1.*  FAST - National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences has a
zero-tolerance policy regarding the use of unfair means. Mobile phones and
smart watches are strictly not allowed in the examination hall.  If mobile
phones or smart watches are brought into the examination hall, then they
should be put in the book bag and the bag should be kept at the front of
the examination hall.  If the student is caught in possession of a mobile
phone or a smartwatch during the examination, it would be considered as use
of unfair means, irrespective of whether the mobile phone is on or off, a
smartphone or a feature phone.



*2.*  Students can only bring a transparent pouch/ pencil box to the seat
of the examination.



*3.*  Non-programmable, non-graphing calculators are allowed in
the examination hall for relevant courses only unless prohibited by the
course instructor.



*4.*  Students are required to sit according to the seating plan. The
invigilator can reallocate any student from their designated seat.



*5.*  Students are required to search for the examination seat and the
surrounding area prior to taking a seat.  If they find any paper or some
writing on the seat/desk, they must report it to the invigilator
immediately.  If caught during the exam, they will be deemed responsible
for it.



*6.*  Students are not allowed to raise their voices during the exam.  In
case of any need, they will raise their hands to call the attention of the
invigilator.



*7.*  The following actions are strictly prohibited during the examination



*        a.*  Sharing anything such as calculators, papers, pencils,
rubber, etc.



*        b.*  Disassembling the answer book by removing the staples.



*        c. * Tearing any portion from the question book.


*        d. * Students are not allowed to raise their voices during
the exam in the corridors.



*8.*  During the examination, students are not allowed to take the question
paper and answer book out of the examination hall in any case.



*9.* Students are not allowed to continue writing after the
examiner/invigilator announces, âThe time is over, put your pens downâ.



*10.*  Students may wish to pace themselves with their own watches, but the
invigilator will be the official timekeeper of the examination.



*11.*  Examination days will be considered normal routine days, and hence,
the dress code should be strictly followed during the exams. Students
violating the dress code will not be allowed to sit in the exams. No
re-take applications will be entertained in such cases.



*12.* Students are not allowed to go to the washroom during the exam.  In
case of an emergency, an attendant would escort them to the washroom.



*13.* Students are requested to bring their own water bottles to
the examination hall.  Water bottles should be transparent.



*Any violation of the above rules will be entered in the invigilation
report and the case will be sent to the disciplinary committee for
appropriate disciplinary action.*

Dear Students,

I hope this message finds you well. As we continually strive to improve the
quality of education at our campus, your feedback is crucial in helping us
assess and enhance both our courses and the performance of our faculty.

We kindly request you to take a few moments to share your honest opinions
regarding the courses you have taken this semester and the
instructors/faculty who taught them. Your feedback will remain anonymous
and will be used to identify areas for improvement and ensure that we
provide you with the best learning experience possible.

Remember to choose the proper option from the drop down menu for each
question, i.e.,  Highly satisfied or Highly dissatisfied or in between.

We hope to receive feedback from each one of you to improve the teaching
and learning environment for you.

Regards

Dr. Zulfiqar Ali Memon
Director

*EXAMINATION RULES*




*1.*  FAST - National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences has a
zero-tolerance policy regarding the use of unfair means. Mobile phones and
smart watches are strictly not allowed in the examination hall.  If mobile
phones or smart watches are brought in the examination hall, then they
should be put in the book bag and the bag be kept at the front of
the examination hall.  If the student is caught in possession of a mobile
phone or a smartwatch during the examination, it would be considered as use
of unfair means, irrespective of whether the mobile phone is on or off, a
smartphone or a feature phone.



*2.*  Students can only bring a transparent pouch/ pencil box to the seat
of examination.



*3.*  Non-programmable, non-graphing calculators are allowed in
the examination hall for relevant courses only unless prohibited by the
course instructor.



*4.*  Students are required to sit according to the seating plan. The
invigilator can reallocate any student from their designated seat.



*5.*  Students are required to search for the examination seat and the
surrounding area prior to taking a seat.  If they find any paper or some
writing on the seat/desk, they must report it to the invigilator
immediately.  If caught during the exam, they will be deemed responsible
for it.



*6.*  Students are not allowed to raise their voices during the exam.  In
case of any need, they will raise their hands to call the attention of the
invigilator.



*7.*  The following actions are strictly prohibited during the examination



*        a.*  Sharing anything such as calculators, papers, pencils,
rubber, etc.



*        b.*  Disassembling the answer book by removing the staples.



*        c. * Tearing any portion from the question book.


*        d. * Students are not allowed to raise their voices during
the exam in the corridors.



*8.*  During the examination, students are not allowed to take the question
paper and answer book out of the examination hall in any case.



*9.* Students are not allowed to continue writing after the
examiner/invigilator announces, âThe time is over, put your pens downâ.



*10.*  Students may wish to pace themselves with their own watches, but the
invigilator will be the official timekeeper of the examination.



*11.*  Examination days will be considered normal routine days and hence
the dress code should be strictly followed during the exams. Students
violating the dress code will not be allowed to sit in the exams. No
re-take applications will be entertained in such cases.



*12.* Students are not allowed to go to the washroom during the exam.  In
case of an emergency, an attendant would escort them to the washroom.



*13.* Students are requested to bring their own water bottles to
the examination hall.  Water bottles should be transparent.



*Any violation of the above rules will be entered in the invigilation
report and the case will be sent to the disciplinary committee for
appropriate disciplinary action.*






*Regards,*



*Academics Department*

*FAST National University of  Computer and Emerging Science*
*Karachi Campus*

*Midterms and Final Examinations:*

*Eligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Marriage (self or sibling)

Â·         Severe illness requiring hospitalization

Â·         Death of an immediate family member

Â·         Severe injury affecting exam attendance

Â·         Iqama renewal or ISSB examination dates coinciding with the exam

Â·         Religious events with fixed dates (e.g., Hajj)

Â·         If you have more than 2 exams on the same day / slot during
the Exams.

*Ineligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Habitual applicants (more than 5 requests)

Â·         Applications with incomplete documentation

Â·         Minor illnesses (cold, flu, etc.)

Â·         Religious events with flexible dates (e.g., Umrah, Aitekaf)

Â·         Marriage of cousins or distant relatives

Â·         Any other reasons not covered in the eligibility criteria

*Important Notes:*

Â·         Students must submit their applications via *FLEX* with *supporting
documents* within the deadline. (No application will be considered manually
or after the deadline).

Â·         Those traveling for a valid reason may take the exam at a remote
campus on the same day and time as their base campus.

Â·         A Faculty Committee shall examine the student's request for a
repeat test/exam If retake of the final exam is allowed, it shall be held
as soon as possible, but not later than one week before the start of
next semester.

Â·         The final decision rests with the Campus Committee and the Campus
Director.



*Retake Exam Fee:*

The retake exam fee is payable before the examination in all the
above-mentioned cases. The late examination fee will be Rs. 2000/-
per exam. Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an application fee.
This is non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be charged on
applications, which have been approved.

VLAN 20 â 192.12.35.0

creation.

*One Week Fully Funded Trip to Thailand to meet Eminent Scientists & Nobel
Laureates by Pakistan Science Foundation Pakistan **Asian Science Camp
(ASC)-2025 at Suranaree University of Technology, Nakorn Ratchasima,
Thailand from 31 July to 06 August, 2025 **Only for First year & Second
Year University/ Institute Students in Pakistan*

* Meet Nobel Laureates in Thailand â Fully Funded Asian Science Camp 2025
for Pakistani Students *

PSF is sponsoring young students for participation in Asian Science Camp
(ASC) where the young students can share their ideas and projects with
fellow students and eminent scientists/Nobel Laureates. The activities
include lectures/demonstrations from leading scientists, visits to
industrial sites, research centers, scientific institutions/organizations,
world class laboratories and universities.

The idea of the Asian Science Camp (ASC) was co-proposed in September 2005,
following the Lindau Science Meeting, by Professor Yuan-Tseh Lee from
Taiwan, the 1986 Nobel Laureate in Chemistry, and Professor Masatoshi
Koshiba from Japan, the 2002 Nobel Laureate in Physics.

 The 15th Asian Science Camp-2025 is going to be from 31st July- 6th
August, 2025 at Suranaree University of Technology, Nakorn Ratchasima,
Thailand. PSF is inviting applications from young Pakistani science
students to participate in the 15th Asian Science Camp (ASC-2025).

   - Interested young students, having age between 17-22 years on 31st
   July, 2025 & regular science students of BS/B.Sc./B.E/MBBS in (1st/2nd year
   only) (1st, 2nd, 3rd or 4th semester students only) having 1st Division in
   board/university.
   - The applicant must be a regular science student in a public or private
   sector (Govt. recognized) institution having proficiency in written and
   spoken English.
   - Short listed students, after initial screening on the basis of
   educational qualifications/age will be called for written test, interview/
   presentation at Islamabad, Lahore, Karachi, Quetta and Peshawar as per
   their convenience.
   - 8 students will be selected for ASC-2025. Air travel will be covered
   by PSF While accommodation and local hospitality will be provided by the
   organizers.
   - No TA/DA will be provided to the students appearing for
   test/interview.
   - *Last date for receipt of the application is 3rd April, 2025.*
   - Incomplete/applications received after the closing date shall not be
   entertained.

Dear Students,



Please note the following Missed Exam Policy:



*Missed Quizzes and Assignments:*

If a student misses a quiz or assignment, they will be awarded zero marks
for that particular assessment.

*Midterms and Final Examinations:*

There is a provision for a retake in the case of:

*Eligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Marriage (self or sibling)

Â·         Severe illness requiring hospitalization

Â·         Death of an immediate family member

Â·         Severe injury affecting exam attendance

Â·         Iqama renewal or ISSB examination dates coinciding with the exam

Â·         Religious events with fixed dates (e.g., Hajj)

Â·         If you have more than 2 exams on the same day / slot during
the Exams.

*Ineligible Cases for Retake Examination:*

Â·         Habitual applicants (more than 5 requests)

Â·         Applications with incomplete documentation

Â·         Minor illnesses (cold, flu, etc.)

Â·         Religious events with flexible dates (e.g., Umrah, Aitekaf)

Â·         Marriage of cousins or distant relatives

Â·         Any other reasons not covered in the eligibility criteria

*Important Notes:*

Â·         Students must submit their applications via *FLEX* with *supporting
documents* within the deadline. (No application will be considered manually
or after the deadline).

Â·         Those traveling for a valid reason may take the exam at a remote
campus on the same day and time as their base campus.

Â·         A Faculty Committee shall examine the student's request for a
repeat test/exam . If retake of the final exam is allowed, it shall be held
as soon as possible, but not later than one week before the start of the
next semester.

Â·         The final decision rests with the Campus Committee and the Campus
Director.



*Retake Exam Fee:*

The retake exam fee is payable before the examination in all the
above-mentioned cases. The late examination fee will be Rs. 2000/-
per exam. Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an application fee.
This is non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be charged on
applications that have been approved.




*Regards,*



*Academics Department*

*FAST National University of  Computer and Emerging Sciences*
*Karachi Campus*

*EXAMINATION RULES*




*1.*  FAST - National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences has a
zero-tolerance policy regarding the use of unfair means. Mobile phones and
smart watches are strictly not allowed in the examination hall.  If mobile
phones or smart watches are brought in the examination hall, then they
should be put in the book bag and the bag be kept at the front of
the examination hall.  If the student is caught in possession of a mobile
phone or a smartwatch during the examination, it would be considered as use
of unfair means, irrespective of whether the mobile phone is on or off, a
smartphone or a feature phone.



*2.*  Students can only bring a transparent pouch/ pencil box to the seat
of examination.



*3.*  Non-programmable, non-graphing calculators are allowed in
the examination hall for relevant courses only unless prohibited by the
course instructor.



*4.*  Students are required to sit according to the seating plan. The
invigilator can reallocate any student from their designated seat.



*5.*  Students are required to search for the examination seat and the
surrounding area prior to taking a seat.  If they find any paper or some
writing on the seat/desk, they must report it to the invigilator
immediately.  If caught during the exam, they will be deemed responsible
for it.



*6.*  Students are not allowed to raise their voices during the exam.  In
case of any need, they will raise their hands to call the attention of the
invigilator.



*7.*  The following actions are strictly prohibited during the examination



*        a.*  Sharing anything such as calculators, papers, pencils,
rubber, etc.



*        b.*  Disassembling the answer book by removing the staples.



*        c. * Tearing any portion from the question book.


*        d. * Students are not allowed to raise their voices during
the exam in the corridors.



*8.*  During the examination, students are not allowed to take the question
paper and answer book out of the examination hall in any case.



*9.* Students are not allowed to continue writing after the
examiner/invigilator announces, âThe time is over, put your pens downâ.



*10.*  Students may wish to pace themselves with their own watches, but the
invigilator will be the official timekeeper of the examination.



*11.*  Examination days will be considered normal routine days and hence
the dress code should be strictly followed during the exams. Students
violating the dress code will not be allowed to sit in the exams. No
re-take applications will be entertained in such cases.



*12.* Students are not allowed to go to the washroom during the exam.  In
case of an emergency, an attendant would escort them to the washroom.



*13.* Students are requested to bring their own water bottles to
the examination hall.  Water bottles should be transparent.



*Any violation of the above rules will be entered in the invigilation
report and the case will be sent to the disciplinary committee for
appropriate disciplinary action.*

*Teach For Pakistan* is dedicated to addressing educational inequity by
cultivating a network of leaders through its highly selective Fellowship
Program . This *full-time,
paid initiative* recruits top graduates from Pakistanâs leading
universities, such as *FAST University*, and provides them with a rigorous
Leadership Development program. Fellows work at the grassroots level to
drive meaningful educational reform while gaining the skills and context
needed to create long-term systemic change. The program envisions a future
where these leaders, equipped with their experiences, will hold influential
positions and make decisions that shape the nationâs progress. Alumni
 of the Fellowship have gone
on to achieve remarkable success, including prestigious scholarships like
*Fulbright*, admission to top graduate schools such as *Harvard*, and
impactful roles in organizations like *UNDP*, where they continue to tackle
educational inequity.

Fellows* currently placed in government schools across Karachi and

students* from all disciplines. This session will outline the Fellowship
application process, provide an opportunity to interact with the Lead
Recruiter, and inspire students to join a movement that ensures every child
in Pakistan receives a quality education, fostering thoughtful and
compassionate future citizens.

*Attention BS Students*
Dear Students,
This is to inform you that the *Retake of Missed Midterm I Spring 2025
Application* process is now open. Those students who have missed their
exams can submit their Application on Flex.
*Last date to apply for Retake*: *Friday, February 28, 2025.*
*Please note that no application will be accepted after the deadline. Only
Flex applications will be entertained.*
*Missed Exam Policy:*
*Missed Quizzes and Assignments:*
If a student misses a quiz or assignment, they will be awarded zero marks
for that particular assessment.
*Midterms and Final Examinations:*
There is a provision for a retake, in the case of:
1. Student's illness (hospitalization, a valid hospitalization
certificate is
required)
2. Serious Accident
3. Death in the immediate family
4. If you have more than 2 exams on the same day during the Exams.
A Faculty Committee shall examine the student's request for a repeat
test/exam If retake of the final exam is allowed, it shall be held as soon
as possible, but not later than one week before the start of next semester.
*Retake Exam Fee:*
Retake exam fee is payable before the examination in all the
above-mentioned cases. The late examination fee will be Rs. 2000/-
per exam. Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an application fee.
This is non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be charged on
applications, which have been approved.
*Regards,*

*Teach For Pakistan* is dedicated to addressing educational inequity by
cultivating a network of leaders through its highly selective Fellowship
Program . This *full-time,
paid initiative* recruits top graduates from Pakistanâs leading
universities, such as *FAST University*, and provides them with a rigorous
Leadership Development program. Fellows work at the grassroots level to
drive meaningful educational reform while gaining the skills and context
needed to create long-term systemic change. The program envisions a future
where these leaders, equipped with their experiences, will hold influential
positions and make decisions that shape the nationâs progress. Alumni
 of the Fellowship have gone
on to achieve remarkable success, including prestigious scholarships like
*Fulbright*, admission to top graduate schools such as *Harvard*, and
impactful roles in organizations like *UNDP*, where they continue to tackle
educational inequity.

As part of the global Teach For All  network, *Teach
For Pakistan* has already made significant strides, with *150 Fellows*
currently placed in government schools across Karachi and Islamabad, and *302
Alumni* impacting over *26,000 children in 92 schools*. The organization is
now recruiting for its *2025 Fellowship*, with the application deadline set
for *March 16th*. To engage potential candidates, an Information Session is
proposed at FAST University, targeting *final-year students* from all
disciplines. This session will outline the Fellowship application process,
provide an opportunity to interact with the Lead Recruiter, and inspire
students to join a movement that ensures every child in Pakistan receives a
quality education, fostering thoughtful and compassionate future citizens.

Teaching Assistant (TA) Application - Spring 2025

Dear All,

Please read carefully, before filling the application:

- A student can only work either as a Student Lab Assistant (SLA) or TA.
You cannot opt for both.
- Those students who have already been TA are not eligible to apply.
- 1st Priority will be given to 21 batch students
- 2nd Priority will be given to 22 batch students
- 3rd priority will be given to veterans
- Minimum Grade should be B+
- Make sure to submit the form using your NU student ID
- TA has to check at least 6 assessments (quizzes + assignments). A course
project (if any) is equivalent to 2 assessments.

- In case of online assignment submissions by the students, the TA has to
properly comment/assess the assignment in electronic format while grading.

- Less than 6 assessments will be paid less proportionally.

Payment will be made as per the following scheme:  Checking 6 assessments
of 1 student will pay you:
1)  Rs. 250 for EE/OBE courses
2) Rs. 190 for MG courses
3) Rs. 150 for Math, Physics & Statistics courses

- S&H courses in English, Pak Studies, Islamic Studies and Psychology are
not eligible for TAs.

Dear Students,
We are excited to share an excellent career opportunity with you. Below are the details:
Company Information

Company: VisionBase
Job Title: UI/UX Developer/Designer
Job Type: Onsite

Job Description
VisionBase, a UK origin company, is expanding and we're looking for dynamic, young, and hardworking individuals to join our Karachi based team. Whether you have experience or are just starting out, we want to hear from you! Why Join VisionBase?Innovative Projects: Work on exciting projects with a talented team. - Career Growth: Opportunities for learning and advancement. - Global Impact: Collaborate with security forces in many countries. If you're ready for new challenges, join us at VisionBase. 
Qualifications
UI Mark-up Languages: Experience with UI mark-up languages like HTML, XAML, or QML is required.UI Frameworks: Good grasp of WPF, Qt (QML), or similar UI frameworks is required.Version Control: Hands-on experience with Git or other version control systems.Design Translation: Ability to translate wireframes, prototypes, and visual designs into clean, functional frontend code.UI Design Tools: Proficiency with design tools like Figma or others.Architectural Knowledge: Familiarity with architectural patterns such as MVVM, MVC, or similar frameworks is a plus.User Experience: A solid understanding of UX principles, including user flows, interaction design, and accessibility standards.  Bonus Skills:Knowledge of animation and motion design principles for a more dynamic UI.
Key Responsibilities
Design and improve Windows desktop apps. Apply user-centered design principles to create intuitive, user-friendly interfaces.Design and develop wireframes, prototypes, and visual designs using tools like Figma or others.Conduct and participate in usability testing and user research to refine design solutions. Implement designs within UI frameworks such as WPF or Qt/QML.Ensure that designs align with company branding, user needs, and technical specifications. Create responsive and accessible UI components to ensure a seamless user experience across different screen sizes and resolutions. 
Apply Now
Don't miss this opportunity! You can apply by:
Sending an email to: nagehan.baser@visionbase.co.uk
We wish you the best of luck in your career journey!

Best Regards,
    Industrial Liaison/Career Services Office
    021 111 128 128 ext. 184

and International Cooperation and University Professors with at least

can go for it*

=======
You can apply in it by only one of the two ways for any of the given below
modalities

*1) Embassy track*

*2) University Track*

=========

*1) Embassy Track*

*Under Embassy track you can apply for any of these 02 programs*

   1. *Masters *(full degree)
   2. *PhD *(full degree)

You will find the deadlines of applications for GKS from Embassy of Korea
in Pakistan and apply there with documents required. Embassy normally
invites students with high CGPAs and IELTS/ TOEFL scores normally and
selects final number of students from the list. But it is not the exact
requirement for Teachers or Researchers.

*The deadline to apply will be announced soon by the embassy and this post
will be updated with links of embassy. See yours country Korean Embassy
yourself*

Details about Embassy Track

Will be Updated soon

You can apply for full Masters degree in South Korea according to the
process given in the guide to get nominated by the Korean embassy in
Islamabad. If you apply through this track you cannot apply by university
track

*b. PhD*

You can apply for full PhD degree in South Korea to according to the
process given in the guide to get nominated by Korean embassy in Islamabad.
If you apply through this track you cannot apply by university track

*Masters and Diploma Fully Funded Scholarships in 05 Brunei Universities
at Brunei Darussalam by Brunei Govt. in almost Every Field/Major*

The Government of Brunei Darussalam is offering scholarships to foreign
students for the 2025/2026 academic session. These scholarships provide
opportunities to pursue Diploma and Postgraduate Master's Degree programs
at several prestigious institutions in Brunei.

*Participating Institutions:*

   1. *Universiti Brunei Darussalam (UBD)* 
   2. *Universiti Islam Sultan Sharif Ali (UNISSA)* 
   3. *Universiti Teknologi Brunei (UTB)* 
   4. *Kolej Universiti Perguruan Ugama Seri Begawan (KUPU SB)*
   
   5. *Politeknik Brunei (PB)* 

*Degree Levels:*

   - Diploma
   - Post-graduate Degree Programs


*Program Period:*

   - Diploma: 03 Years
   - Master Degree: 12 Months Or 24 Months

*Eligibility Criteria:*

   - *Age Requirements:*
   -
      - Applicants for Diploma programs must not exceed 25 years of age by
      July 1, 2025.
      - Applicants for Postgraduate Master's Degree programs must not
      exceed 35 years of age by the same date.
   - *English Proficiency:*
   -
      - A minimum of Credit 6 in English at GCE 'O' Level, or
      - Grade 'C' in IGCSE English (as a second language), or
      - An IELTS score of 6.0, or
      - A TOEFL score of at least 550.
   - *Nationality:*
   -
      - The scholarship is primarily intended for international students
      who have not previously studied in Brunei.

*Scholarship Benefits:*

   - Full exemption from tuition fees, including acceptance, examination,
   registration, and orientation fees.
   - Economy class air tickets to and from Brunei at the start and end of
   the program.
   - Monthly personal allowance of BND$500.00 (500 US $).
   - Monthly meals allowance of BND$150.00 (112 US $).
   - Annual book allowance of BND$600.00 (445 US $).
   - Accommodation at the respective institution's residential college.
   - Baggage allowance for shipment of personal effects upon completion of
   the program:
   -
      - BND$250.00 to ASEAN countries.
      - BND$500.00 to non-ASEAN countries.
   - Comprehensive insurance coverage for the duration of the scholarship.

*Important Dates:*

   - *Application Deadline:* February 15, 2025.


For details: see here :
https://gradwinner.com/articles/brunei-government-scholarships-2025

*Dear Students,*

Please read carefully before filling up the application form:

*Student Lab Assistant (SLA Demonstrator)* is required for *Programming
Fundamentals (PF Lab - 1 vacancy)*, *Object Oriented Programming (OOP Lab -
16 vacancies)*, and *Data Structures (DS Lab - 1 vacancy)* in
*Spring 2025 Semester*.

   - *Student Lab Assistants* are required to assist the Lab Instructors in
   conducting the Labs (3 hours weekly).
   - *Eligibility*: Only *Batch 21* (CS, SE, CY, AI) and *Batch 22* (CS,
   SE, CY, AI) students who have *A+, A, or A-* (in PF, OOP, or DS Theory)
   are eligible to apply.
   - *Per hour rate*: Rs. 500/- (one lab consists of 3 hours). *Total
   Amount for one Lab = Rs. 1500/-*.
   - *Lab Duration*: You will be required to teach around 42 hours (i.e. 14
   weeks x 3 hours).
   - *Payment*: Payment will be made after the conclusion of the semester,
   upon verification by your Lab Course Teacher.
   - *Selection Criteria*: If there are more applicants than vacancies, the
   applicant list will be sorted according to the applicant's *CGPA* and *Grade
   obtained* in that subject.
   - *Application Limit*: You can apply for only 1 subject from the
   above-mentioned Labs during the semester.
   - *Simultaneous Appointments*: Ensure that you are not appointed as both
   SLA and STA in the same semester.
   - *Campus Requirement*: SLAs should be responsible for visiting campus
   to conduct the Lab as per the timetable schedule, even on their off
days. *No
   excuses will be entertained*.
   - *Timetable Clash*: In case of a clash between your regular class time
   and the time of OOP/PF/DS lab assigned, the Student Lab Assistant will have
   to manage the timetable clash themselves. The University is *not
   responsible for attendance matters*.

*Application Form Link*: Application Form for Student Lab Assistant (SLA)
Spring 2025 - Google Forms


*Last Date to Apply*: *January 30th, 2025, at 11:59 PM*.

For any queries related to the *Student Lab Assistant (SLA) Application*,
please contact:

   - *Mr. Muhammad Waheeb Khan* (waheeb.khan@nu.edu.pk) or
   - *Anwar Ali Memon* (anwar.ali@nu.edu.pk)
   *Office Hours*: 8:00 am - 4:00 pm FSC Secretariat, Academics Block I (CS
   Block).




*Regards,*



*Academics Department*

*FAST National University of  Computer and Emerging Sciences*
*Karachi Campus*

This is to inform you that the retake of the Final exam request will be
activated in flex on 28 December,2024..


*The last date to apply for Retake is Tuesday, December 31st, 2024.*



Students who have missed any of their Final exams can apply on flex during
the above-mentioned dates.



*Below is the policy for retake of missed exams:*



*Missed Quizzes and Assignments:*

If a student misses a quiz or assignment, they will be awarded zero marks
for that particular assessment.

*Midterms and Final Examinations:*

There is a provision for a retake, in the case of:

*1.       Student's illness (hospitalization, a valid hospitalization
certificate is *

*          required)*

*2.       Serious Accident*

*3.       Death in the immediate family*

A Faculty Committee shall examine the request of the student for
a repeat test/exam If a retake of the Final exam is allowed, it shall be
held as soon as possible

*Retake Exam Fee:*

Retake exam fee is payable before the examination. The late examination fee
will be Rs. 2000/- per exam. Out of this, Rs. 1000/- will be charged as an
application fee. This is non-refundable. The remaining Rs. 1000/- will be
charged on applications, which have been approved.

Hi -Â it's Nick Singh from DataLemur / Ace the DS Interview here to air out my dirty laundry:

**Â  My girlfriend hates me because I tell her she's NOTÂ special **

She's a full-time Data Analyst who's simultaneously searching for a new job, and she'llÂ complain to me about problems like:

**"I applied to 30 jobs but only got 1 interview"

"This open job has senior analyst expectations, butÂ junior analyst pay"

"I can't find time to study for interviews dueÂ to my hectic schedule"**

I constantly remind her she's not special, everyone has these issues,Â and she HATES hearing that.

(yes, I get it, she's looking for sympathy, wants to feelÂ heard, etc.)Â 

But that's not going to stop me from ranting about:

* why the "â¨I'm specialâ¨" mindset isÂ detrimental

* why thinking your NOT being special is a GOOD thing for tech careersÂ 

* 5 amazing career advice resources from different leaders in tech that'llÂ helpÂ 98.9% of people (regardless of their uniqueÂ backgrounds)

****Special Snowflake SyndromeÂ âï¸****

Growing up inÂ 90s America, IÂ had motivational posters like this one in most of my classrooms:

My teachers taught me that there were different "learning styles"... and that we all learn uniquely.Â 

They told me that Kyle, my middle-school bully, isn't dumbÂ because he's in 8th grade and can't read and write... he's just a musical auditory learner who's actually a genius because he can play the guitar.Â 

Fast forward to 2023, and psychologists have debunked all this "my brain learns differently" nonsense, and my bully /Â auditory genius classmate Kyle works the Taco Bell drive thru.

We're not all special snowflakes, who learn in our own unique ways.

We're not all special snowflakes, with unique personalities & interests.Â 

(swipe on Tinder for 2 minutes to see how "unique" your passion for dogs / the office / tacos / pizza / traveling are)

Similarly, you're not a special snowflake with totally unique career challenges!

I know this from having done hundreds of 1:1 career coaching sessions https://nicksingh79965.acemlna.com/lt.php?x=3TZy~GE6KaKfEHz-_Q1GUuRzAX-pvN-gkuovY5jMIFia5XKryEy.yuJt5X6mmNE~j-s008QGWqUP6XF5ytPL with people from a variety of backgrounds, ages, and countries - it all boils down to the same struggles:

* How do I find a careerÂ that I'll love

* How do I convince others to give me that interview / job / promotion

****You're Not Special and that's GOOD****
Knowing you're not facing special problems is an EMPOWERING mindset to have when you're grinding on the job hunt or trying to climb the career Â Ì¶lÌ¶aÌ¶dÌ¶dÌ¶eÌ¶rÌ¶ jungle gym https://nicksingh79965.acemlna.com/lt.php?x=3TZy~GE6KaKfEHz-_Q1GUuRzAX-pvN-gkuovY5jMIFia5XKryEy.yuJt5X6mmNE~j-s108QGWqUP6XF5ytPL.Â 

Realizing your career struggles aren'tÂ special means:

* you're more open to learning from other's experiences and wisdom, rather than discounting their advice because their journey doesn't exactly match up to your own

* you're less likely to have unrealistic expectations for learning & career growth, which will save you a ton of frustration and make you more patient

* you'll be more receptive to hearing how others faced similar challenges and overcame them, which will provide you comfort and help you be resilient during difficult times

Dear All,

This is to inform you that the departure for the DECS Annual Tour is
scheduled for *5th January at 8:30 PM*. Please make sure to arrive on time,
as the train will not wait for latecomers.

Attached are the Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and Code of Conduct
for the tour. Kindly review these carefully and adhere to them:

   1. *Mandatory Documents*: Carry your original CNIC, university ID, and
   the tour receipt to board the train.
   2. *Liability*: DECS and FAST-NUCES are not responsible for any
   accidents, loss of life, or property. Ensure your belongings are secure.
   3. *Respect and Compliance*: Follow all management instructions and
   treat staff courteously.
   4. *Punctuality*: Train will not wait for latecomers.
   5. *Participation*: Joining or leaving the tour midway is not permitted.
   6. *Prohibited Items*: Do not bring weapons, sharp objects, or dangerous
   items.
   7. *Meals*: Breakfast and dinner will be served on schedule. Be punctual
   to avoid inconvenience.
   8. *Behavior*: Maintain respectful conduct, particularly toward the
   opposite gender, and avoid harassment or inappropriate actions.
   9. *Cultural Norms*: Gender interactions should align with societal and
   cultural norms.
   10. *Safety and Facilities*: Use provided facilities responsibly and
   follow management guidelines.
   11. *Illegal Activities*: Engaging in illegal activities or possessing
   drugs will result in legal consequences.
   12. *Smoking/Vaping*: Smoking or vaping is prohibited in public and
   shared areas. Violators will face penalties.
   13. *Discipline*: Violations may result in fines or academic penalties,
   including semester termination.
   14. *Additional Costs*: Personal expenses beyond the provided services
   are your responsibility.

Adherence to these guidelines is essential to ensure a smooth and enjoyable
experience for everyone. Should you have any questions, feel free to reach
out.

Looking forward to an incredible tour together!

For any queries feel free to contact us at the given numbers below:

*Annas : 0324-2255467Hamza: 0307-2261839*

Regards,
Team DECS.

Join us in building innovative solutions that empower decision-making and

Proficiency in MERN, JavaScript, React, and Python.

Strong API integration and data validation skills.

Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Preferred:
Experience with dashboards and data visualization tools.
Knowledge of automation tools for workflow optimization.

Hi - if you want a kick-ass career in tech, you need to think about your career 

**non-linearly**.

Before I share stories of Data Scientists and Software Engineers at 

**Airbnb** & 

**Spotify**Â who followed non-linear career paths, let's analyze Sheryl Sandberg's 

**weird** journey to FacebookÂ 

**COO.Â **

In 2000, Sheryl worked as Chief of Staff to Larry Summers at the US Treasury Department - a job which had nothing to do with tech/advertising/sales.

However, In 2001, Google CEO Eric Schmidt was impressed by her intellect, so tried to recruit her.

Sheryl for the longest time was reluctant to join this small startupÂ because it looked like a step DOWN for her.

In hindsight, she's glad she made the leap: she crushed the Google job, became VP of Ads, and grew her org from 4 to 4,000 employees in six short years .Â 

Then, Zuck poached her to become COO at Facebook, which is how she got her net-worth of $1.8 billion.

It's wild to think that her switch into tech almost didn't happen because of her preconceived notions about climbing a traditional career ladder.

That's why she now preaches about the career jungle gym:

The path forward in your career might not be straight ahead; we need to be open to a sideways move, maybe even a step back, to ultimately realize our full potential.Â 

This is known as swinging in the career jungle gym, or following the career lattice (rather than climbing the corporate ladder).Â 

****

****Non-Linear Path AdvantagesÂ ****Non-linear career paths, while circuitous and stressful, have two big advantages:Â Â 

**#1 - Non-Linearity BuildsÂ ResilienceÂ **

Non-linear paths force you to get comfortable with uncertainty and adapting to new work challenges, and overall become mentally tougher.

Simply put, if you take control and f*** up your own career journey with twists and turns, you'll be a lot less scared of layoffs or getting fired because you've dealt with big career changes already.Â 

**#2Â - Non-LinearityÂ Builds CEOÂ SkillsÂ **

A non-linear path helps you build theÂ broadÂ range of experiences and skills needed to be a CEO or entrepreneur; something that'll never happen working inÂ one narrow discipline.Â 

This diverse skill set helps you open up new, unexpected paths into the C-suite.

****Non-Linear Paths to Airbnb & Spotify****
To inspire you, here's some examples of people who've had kick-ass, non-linear careers in tech:

****My Non-Linear CareerÂ ****
I can personally attest to the power of non-linear careers, because I'm lucky enough to have one - but it wasn't always this way!

Starting out my career at Facebook, I had a linear view of careers, and at age 22 I fully expected to just do technical roles at FAANG and collect increasingly bigger paychecks till I chose to retire.Â
